    <node id="claim:0005">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Client uploads to Unsorted Records cause duplication: ops must re-upload to the batch</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "it creates a bit of duplication because if it is a matter that requires a sorting session, they, and the clients has uploaded their own records, they uploaded to this folder and then the ops team, they need to go download whatever the clients uploaded from this folder, go back to the Matter dashboard", "ts": 253.4, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "they need to go and they need to upload the same folders that were uploaded here into the batch.", "ts": 280.7, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:02"]</data>
      <data key="d20">When clients upload records to the Unsorted Records folder and a sorting session is required, the ops team must manually re-download and re-upload those records into the batch, causing duplicated effort.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d25">253.4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0006">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Apryse was previously named PDFTron; it is the same viewer</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "PDF Tron. Yeah, yeah, yeah. Is that what it, okay.", "ts": 457.5, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "So apparently it's still the same viewer, just different name.", "ts": 469.5, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:03"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The records viewer tool Apryse was previously called PDFTron; the underlying viewer technology is the same, only the name changed.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
