      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d25">3302.2</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0053">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Expert profile information from the internet is confirmed by the expert on first login</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "once they've given their decision whether they can accept or decline, they get then prompted to confirm their profile information. Because obviously, we want to make sure that the profile information that we got on the expert is accurate.", "ts": 3406.9, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:12"]</data>
      <data key="d20">After an expert responds to a letter of approach, they are prompted to review and confirm the AI-generated profile information, at which point MedBrief treats it as accurate.</data>
