      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "The idea here was for us to use, we tried it with regular expression, but it's too tricky because the claimant name is not always as simple as the claimant name.", "ts": 3609, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "we may need the AM component to do that. So for the moment, it is unfortunately a very manual process", "ts": 3633, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
      <data key="d20">MedBrief tried using regex to auto-replace the claimant name with initials in the letter of approach, but abandoned it because name formats vary; the team concluded an AI component may be needed, so for now it is a manual edit.</data>
