      <data key="d1">MedBrief Match was built quickly under a tight deadline; some features were deliberately left out for the initial Lime release</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "This was created very, very quickly. We, it wasn't created at a very tight deadline. So there's a lot of the stuff that we, we left out just to, to get it out for this client.", "ts": 3779, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "And that was somewhere in March, I think, or beginning of April, we gave it to the client.", "ts": 3790, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
      <data key="d20">MedBrief Match was built under a tight deadline; many features were deliberately omitted to get the initial release to Lime around March or April.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">3779</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0060">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">MedBrief Match is a new revenue stream and has been a long-standing client request</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "it's literally another revenue stream, which is like amazing.", "ts": 3862, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "it's something that's been requested from clients in the past before is, you know, why can't we look for experts via make briefs?", "ts": 4868, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14", "chapter:15"]</data>
      <data key="d20">MedBrief Match represents a new revenue stream and has been a long-standing feature request from clients.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">3862</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0061">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Letter of Approach PDF is encrypted and not sent as email attachment; expert must log in to view and respond</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "the letter of approach PDF is generated, but it's not sent as an attachment in the email. The expert must, they must log on to, to view, view it.", "ts": 3958, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "The reason for that is because it needs to be encrypted, the PDF.", "ts": 3968, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The letter of approach PDF is generated and encrypted; it is not attached to the email sent to the expert. The expert must log in to the platform to view and respond to it.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">3958</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0062">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Whole letter-of-approach process (search, send, expert response) is end-to-end within MedBrief</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "So does the whole process end to end, like the searching for them, sending the letter of approach, does this all happen within MedBrief?", "ts": 4145, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Correct.", "ts": 4167, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The entire expert-matching workflow from search through letter of approach to expert acceptance or decline is conducted within the MedBrief platform, facilitated by system-generated emails.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">4167</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0063">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Claimant name / initials choice propagates to email subject, email body and expert's matter view</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "It applies to the subject line of the email or the content of the email that gets sent to the, to the expert where he will not see the patient or the claimant's full name.", "ts": 4243, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "also when they log in, because he doesn't have access to this matter yet, even though you can see this matter widget, he only still sees the, the initials.", "ts": 4252, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13", "chapter:14"]</data>
      <data key="d20">Selecting initials vs full name in the letter of approach applies throughout: the email subject, email body, and what the expert sees when they log in before being invited to the matter.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">4243</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0064">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Expert must agree to MedBrief terms and conditions to accept, decline, or request more information</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "whether they decline, accept, or they request any more information for them to, to be able to continue, they have to, to have to agree to the terms and conditions, which is a bit risky because if I'm an expert and I'm declining, I don't necessarily want to agree to terms and conditions", "ts": 4371, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "We are trying this and just see, um, hopefully there won't be too much of a drop off.", "ts": 4389, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
      <data key="d20">Regardless of their decision, experts must agree to the MedBrief expert user terms and conditions before they can accept, decline, or request more information.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">4371</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0065">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Risk: requiring T&amp;Cs agreement even for declining experts may cause drop-off</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "which is a bit risky because if I'm an expert and I'm declining, I don't necessarily want to agree to terms and conditions because I'm not, anyway. But we are trying this and just see, um, hopefully there won't be too much of a drop off.", "ts": 4382, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
      <data key="d20">Requiring experts to agree to terms and conditions even when declining is acknowledged as a risk that could cause expert drop-off.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">risk</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">4382</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0066">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Required-information requests loop back to the decision page on every return until accept or decline is given</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "every, every single time they come back and they need to, to give an answer, they will be directed to this page every single time until they give us an accept or decline.", "ts": 4413, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:14"]</data>
      <data key="d20">If an expert requests more information before deciding, they are redirected to the decision page every time they log in until they have given a definitive accept or decline.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">4413</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0067">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Experts frequently reply to the letter of approach email directly rather than logging in, causing a manual copy-paste process</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "experts, they, when they receive a letter of approach by make brief, instead of them logging on to respond to them, to their email, they reply to the email. So at the moment, that's a manual process.", "ts": 4555, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "whoever gets that email needs to, or usually MNE, she needs to update the expert's response accordingly and then copy and paste whatever the email contains into the actual conversations", "ts": 4565, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:15"]</data>
      <data key="d20">It is a known and frequent problem that experts reply to the notification email directly rather than logging into MedBrief; the result is a manual process where staff must copy the email content into the platform conversation.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">4555</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0068">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Letter of instruction is not yet created inside the platform; clients generate it themselves and attach it manually</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "No, it's different. Um, but it is something that we are going to do down the line.", "ts": 4610, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "at the moment, the clients need to generate that themselves.", "ts": 4619, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:15"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The letter of instruction is currently generated outside the platform by the client and manually attached as a message; in-platform creation is planned for the future.</data>
