    <node id="claim:0073">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Disclosures are between opposing law firms (claimant/defendant), not MedBrief-managed</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">Disclosures are where one firm discloses all the records it holds to the opposing firm, whether claimant to defendant or defendant to claimant. This is entirely client-managed and cuts out MedBrief admin.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5204</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "So it's where the one firm discloses all the records that they have to the opposing firm. So whether it's claimant to defendant or defendant to claimant, that's what this is.", "ts": 5204, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "this is not a MedBrief admin thing. This is a client thing. So clients can go and do this themselves.", "ts": 5547, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:17"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0074">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Disclosure fee is approximately £35-£45, payable by either the disclosing or recipient firm</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">MedBrief charges a fee of approximately £35 or £45 for a disclosure. Depending on configuration, this fee can fall on the firm creating the disclosure or on the recipient firm.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5265</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "we do ask a fee, I think it's 35 pounds or 45 pounds for disclosure", "ts": 5265, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "sometimes it's the firm that whose matter this is who's doing the disclosure, sometimes they opt to pay the fee or sometimes it's the recipient fee that needs to pay the fee", "ts": 5272, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:17"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0075">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Disclosure recipients are notified by email and access the limited record set via MedBrief login</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">When a disclosure is confirmed, recipients receive an email. Existing MedBrief users get a direct login link; new users are prompted to activate their profile by choosing a password. They then see only the document and radiology viewers limited to the disclosed records.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5350</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "an email will go out to all the parties that have been invited, as well as the person who created this invitation or disclosure", "ts": 5350, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "If they're not already a user on MedBrief based on that email address, then they get asked to activate their profile where they just choose a password.", "ts": 5401, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "they get to see the document viewer and the radiology viewer, et cetera, but all limited to just the stuff that's been disclosed", "ts": 5409, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:17"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0076">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Disclosure status lifecycle is: pending → processing → active</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">After a disclosure is confirmed it starts with a status of 'pending', then moves to 'processing', and finally becomes 'active'. The transition to active takes a little while.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5359</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "it's going to have the status of pending, then processing. And then once it's active, it will update to active. But that takes a little while.", "ts": 5359, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:17"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0077">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Disclosures expire after 30 days and can be reactivated for a further 30 days</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d20">A disclosure has a 30-day validity period from creation. Once it expires it can be reactivated for another 30-day period, and records/users can be updated while active.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5449</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "when a disclosures created, there's a 30-day period before the disclosure actually expires", "ts": 5449, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Once they have expired, they can be reactivated for another 30 days or whatever.", "ts": 5458, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:17"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0078">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Communications tab links emails to a matter via matter reference number or records-request keyword in the subject line</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d20">Any email to or from medical institutions or clients is linked to the relevant matter page if its subject line contains either the matter reference number or the words 'records request'. The tab is only visible to MedBrief admins.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5567</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "as long as it has either the matter reference number or a records request in the subject line, it will link it to this page", "ts": 5587, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "The communications tab is only visible to MedBrief admins.", "ts": 5563, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:18"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0079">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Saved reports drive the ops team's daily workflow across records requests, batches, clinical reports, and new matters</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d20">The reports section (admin-only) contains saved reports used daily by the ops team to identify follow-up work. They cover records requests, batches, clinical reports, additional requests, sorting sessions and matter requests.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5635</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "what determines the workflow of matters that get worked on is determined by the various reports", "ts": 5635, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "They have got saved reports that they use on a daily basis. So they'll have like a daily chase.", "ts": 5669, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "For batches, same thing. For clinical reports, if they need to keep track on what's outstanding, what's overdue, that type of thing, they use the clinical reports.", "ts": 5714, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:18"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0080">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Matter requests report only includes matters created via the matter creation wizard, not legacy-created matters</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">Any new matter created by the matter creation wizard is added to the matter requests report for client services review. Matters created the legacy way are not included.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5816</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "Any new matter that's created by the matter creation wizard, I should correct. If it's created the legacy way, it will not be added here.", "ts": 5816, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:18"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0081">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Firms section is for API-based matter import; only Kennedys currently uses it</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">The Firms section in Manage is not the same as Clients. It is specifically for API-based matter import. Currently only Kennedys uses an API to import matters from their own A-System.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
