      <data key="d4">["chapter:19"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0082">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Clinical sections list has 146 approved entries; unapproved ones accumulate from DocSorter operators adding new values</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">There are 146 approved clinical sections available in the DocSorter dropdown. Operators can add new clinical sections on the fly, which is why the unfiltered list had ~15,000 entries, but only approved ones appear in the dropdown.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">5926</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "there's 146. That's much better. So you get your clinical sections that's approved, that's added to the dropdown whenever they select a clinical section.", "ts": 5950, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "If it's not a clinical section that's in the dropdown, they can obviously add it. And that's why you've seen 15,000 in the original list.", "ts": 5960, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:19"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0083">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Expert agency notification on MedBrief was used previously but is no longer needed</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">MedBrief used to notify expert agencies when an expert linked to their agency was instructed or invited on MedBrief. That notification behaviour has since been removed as it was deemed unnecessary.</data>
      <data key="d21">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">fact</data>
      <data key="d24">False</data>
      <data key="d26">6053</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "we actually used to... notify that particular agency that is linked to that expert that this expert was instructed on MedBrief or invited on MedBrief. But we've since, well, MedBrief matches actually need that.", "ts": 6053, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:19"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="claim:0084">
      <data key="d0">Claim</data>
      <data key="d1">Client-specific billing rates can be configured; current default is 8.5% markup for all clients</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d20">Billing items can be set at a universal rate or per client. The current default is an 8.5% markup applied to all clients, but some clients with preferential sorting rates have client-specific billing items.</data>
