      <data key="d25">119.4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0003">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">MedBrief Insights panel will not go live until the AI team confirms sufficient model accuracy</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "they are reviewing the model of accuracy to see how accurate it is because if it's not very accurate, it's not something we will be able to take live yet until it is.", "ts": 1110.4, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:04"]</data>
      <data key="d20">MedBrief Insights / Ask Alex will not be released to production until the AI team has reviewed and confirmed the model's accuracy is sufficient.</data>
      <data key="d27">["person:chantel-van-wyk"]</data>
      <data key="d29">An inaccurate AI assistant would be harmful to users in a medico-legal context.</data>
      <data key="d28">made</data>
      <data key="d25">1110.4</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0004">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Use bookmarks (or VLM heading fallback) instead of clinical section identification for CER index</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "we first thought about identifying the different clinical sections in the document. But that is very difficult...So instead, what we're doing for now, at least, is we're extracting the bookmarks", "ts": 1222.9, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:05"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The CER index approach pivoted from attempting to identify clinical sections to extracting bookmarks (or headings via VLM as fallback) because clinical section identification by content is too difficult.</data>
      <data key="d27">["person:chantel-van-wyk"]</data>
      <data key="d29">Clinical section identification is too difficult because content varies and multiple sections can appear on one page; bookmarks are familiar to users and already used.</data>
      <data key="d28">made</data>
      <data key="d25">1222.9</data>
      <data key="d30">["Identifying clinical sections by content type"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0005">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Launch CER index on Epic only first, extend to other CER types later</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "we're going to go live with the solution, the CER index, only on Epic. Because for all the computerized electronic records, Epic takes about 70% of them.", "ts": 1647.7, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "So for that reason, we're only going to go with Epic. And then later, we will attempt the other CER types.", "ts": 1663.1, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:05"]</data>
      <data key="d20">The CER index will launch exclusively on Epic, with other CER types attempted later.</data>
      <data key="d27">["person:chantel-van-wyk"]</data>
      <data key="d29">Epic covers approximately 70% of computerised electronic records, making it the highest-value first target.</data>
      <data key="d28">made</data>
      <data key="d25">1647.7</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0006">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Key events not included in MVP; chronology wizard to be built first</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "what we are going to be doing, not for the MVP release, we're going to create a chronology wizard", "ts": 1952.2, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "And then at some point, once we actually can do key events without the help of chronology, then the AI team will add key events as another mode or future for metric insights.", "ts": 2060.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:07"]</data>
      <data key="d20">Key events as an AI-generated output is excluded from the MVP release. A chronology wizard will be built first; key events will be added as a future MedBrief Insights mode once it can be done without relying on an existing chronology.</data>
      <data key="d27">["person:chantel-van-wyk"]</data>
      <data key="d29">Key events is hard to do accurately without a chronology; the chronology wizard must come first to provide structured input.</data>
      <data key="d28">made</data>
      <data key="d25">1952.2</data>
    </node>
