    <node id="decision:0012">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Expert 'instructed' status inferred from invitation event rather than an explicit instructed flag</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "we are using the fact that the moment an expert is invited, we're going to be using that as the instructed status. Because the only time an expert is invited is when they have been instructed.", "ts": 4748, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:15"]</data>
      <data key="d20">In the absence of an explicit instructed status, the system infers instructed status from the moment the expert is invited to the matter.</data>
      <data key="d27">["person:chantel-van-wyk"]</data>
      <data key="d29">An expert is only ever invited after being instructed, making the invite event a reliable proxy.</data>
      <data key="d28">made</data>
      <data key="d26">4748</data>
    </node>
