    <node id="question:0008">
      <data key="d0">Question</data>
      <data key="d1">For sections with dates embedded in content rather than headings, should those dates be extracted to date the section?</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "So in which case we'd want to find it and then date that section.", "ts": 1558.5, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:05"]</data>
      <data key="d37">Where a section has no date in its heading but has dates in content (e.g. Orders only), should MedBrief extract those content dates to date the section?</data>
      <data key="d38">person:rowan-reid</data>
      <data key="d39">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d40">True</data>
      <data key="d41">Yes, ideally, but it is very difficult because content-embedded dates vary in type and meaning; the AI team wants a generalised solution.</data>
      <data key="d42">person:chantel-van-wyk</data>
      <data key="d43">1563.5</data>
      <data key="d44">clarifying</data>
      <data key="d25">1558.5</data>
    </node>
