    <node id="visual:0035">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">Letter of Approach - AI-drafted editor</data>
      <data key="d2">0.9</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "Letter of Approach. Dr Alastair Bint - Freelance GP and General Practice Expert Witness. Matter: Mr Darren Joseph -v- United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust. Matter Number: 2544944.1. Matter Manager: Layla Said. Dear Dr Bint, I act on behalf of [Claimant initials] in relation to a potential clinical negligence claim against United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust. I am writing to enquire whether you would be willing and available to accept instructions in this matter to prepare a report addressing issues of breach of duty and causation. Background: The background facts are as follows... The key issues requiring expert analysis include: 1. The clinical circumstances and management decisions relevant to the alleged breach; 2. The potential causal relationship between the alleged breach and any reported injury or outcome. Records obtained: We have obtained the following medical records to date - [Chapter] pages from the Claimant's GP surgery, [Chapter] pages from [Hospital Trust Name], [Chapter] pages from other relevant providers. [Update required]. Progress of litigation: We are presently at an early stage of the litigation. Helper prompt: 'How did we do with the case summary?'. Buttons: Save &amp; preview, Save draft, Review &amp; send.", "ts": 3831.062, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["chapter:13"]</data>
      <data key="d52">frame-00055.png</data>
      <data key="d53">3831.062</data>
      <data key="d54">app</data>
      <data key="d55">Letter of Approach. Dr Alastair Bint - Freelance GP and General Practice Expert Witness. Matter: Mr Darren Joseph -v- United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust. Matter Number: 2544944.1. Matter Manager: Layla Said. Dear Dr Bint, I act on behalf of [Claimant initials] in relation to a potential clinical negligence claim against United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust. I am writing to enquire whether you would be willing and available to accept instructions in this matter to prepare a report addressing issues of breach of duty and causation. Background: The background facts are as follows... The key issues requiring expert analysis include: 1. The clinical circumstances and management decisions relevant to the alleged breach; 2. The potential causal relationship between the alleged breach and any reported injury or outcome. Records obtained: We have obtained the following medical records to date - [Chapter] pages from the Claimant's GP surgery, [Chapter] pages from [Hospital Trust Name], [Chapter] pages from other relevant providers. [Update required]. Progress of litigation: We are presently at an early stage of the litigation. Helper prompt: 'How did we do with the case summary?'. Buttons: Save &amp; preview, Save draft, Review &amp; send.</data>
      <data key="d31">The Letter of Approach editor for Dr Alastair Bint, an AI-drafted letter with editable sections (Background, Records obtained, Progress of litigation) and inline placeholder tokens such as [Claimant initials] and [Chapter] page references. An 'Ask Alex' style helper bubble ('How did we do with the case summary?') sits over the letter, showing the AI assists drafting and the user reviews and edits before sending.</data>
      <data key="d56">acc9c8c9d8f8f8c0</data>
    </node>
